# Pipeline checklist

## Rule
When a pipeline command terminates (successful Gate 2 approval, explicit `reject`, or HALT), the orchestrator MUST emit a **completion panel** to chat containing:

1. A **phase checklist** showing every phase the command was supposed to run, each with status: `DONE` / `SKIPPED` / `HALTED` / `N/A`.
2. A **summary table** (repos, feature branch, base, working-tree status [`uncommitted`], files changed, review result, JIRA comment id, task-history path). There is no commit SHA — the pipeline never commits.
3. **Next steps** (the developer stages, commits, and pushes: `git add` → `git commit` → `git push` + open MR).

The checklist replaces ad-hoc summaries. It is the developer's single proof that every required phase actually ran.

## Required phases per command

The checklist MUST list these phases in this order. Skipping any phase that is marked **required** is a pipeline bug.

| Phase | `/implement` | `/bugfix` | `/plan` | `/triage` |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| `command-invoked` (developer typed it) | required | required | required | required |
| `jira-agent` | required | required | required | required |
| `ticket-completeness-agent` | required | required | required | required |
| `router-agent` | required | required | required | required |
| `rca-agent` | N/A | required | N/A | N/A |
| `planner-agent` | required | required | required | N/A |
| `Gate 1` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `base-branch-picker-agent` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `coder-agent` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `Review-Readiness Gate` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `review-agents (×14, parallel)` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `review-aggregator → JIRA comment` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `Gate 2` | required | required | N/A | N/A |
| `task-history finalized` | required | required | required | required |

For `/plan` and `/triage` (no code, no gates), the checklist still appears at termination — confirming the read-only run completed.

## Checklist format

Markdown table, one row per phase. Compact. No emoji.

```
| # | Phase                                  | Status |
|---|----------------------------------------|--------|
| 0 | /implement EFP-1423 (invoked)          | DONE   |
| 1 | jira-agent                             | DONE   |
| 2 | ticket-completeness-agent              | DONE   |
| 3 | router-agent                           | DONE   |
| 4 | planner-agent                          | DONE   |
| 5 | Gate 1 (plan + base branches)          | DONE   |
| 6 | base-branch-picker-agent               | DONE   |
| 7 | coder-agent                            | DONE   |
| 8 | Review-Readiness Gate                  | DONE   |
| 9 | review-agents (×14, parallel)          | DONE   |
|10 | review-aggregator → JIRA comment       | DONE (comment 113837) |
|11 | Gate 2                                 | DONE   |
|12 | task-history finalized                 | DONE (ai-brain/task-history/EFP-1423.md) |
```

Status vocabulary:
- `DONE` — phase completed normally.
- `DONE (…)` — completed with a notable artifact id (comment id, file path) in parens.
- `SKIPPED` — phase was not required for this command (use for `rca-agent` row on `/implement` etc.).
- `HALTED` — phase ran and stopped the pipeline.
- `N/A` — phase does not exist for this command.

Phase index `0` is always the command invocation itself (so the developer sees they triggered it).

## Why
Today the developer only sees disembodied PASS/FAIL banners during a run and a free-form summary at the end. Without a fixed checklist:
- It is easy to silently skip a phase (we already had a bug where reviewers were skipped).
- The developer has no clean record of what ran in what order.
- Audit + post-mortem need to reconstruct phases from chat scrollback.

A fixed table at termination makes the skipped phase obvious — `SKIPPED` shows up where `DONE` should — and gives the developer one thing to screenshot for ops/QA.

## Constraints
- The checklist is emitted **once, at termination** — not after each phase. Live progress is the responsibility of [`agent-attribution`](agent-attribution.md) banners.
- Every `required` phase MUST appear with `DONE` (or `HALTED`). If the orchestrator cannot show `DONE` for a required phase, it must mark `HALTED` and not claim success.
- `task-history finalized` is the last row and is **non-skippable** — see [`human-approval-gates`](human-approval-gates.md). The orchestrator MUST verify the file exists at `ai-brain/task-history/<KEY>.md` and that its frontmatter `last-phase` equals the terminating phase before rendering the checklist.
- The completion panel is rendered AFTER the developer's Gate 2 `approve` reply — never before.
- On `reject` or `HALTED`, the orchestrator still emits a checklist with the appropriate statuses + the reason in a `## Halt reason` block below.

## Examples

### Good (successful /implement)
```
| # | Phase                              | Status |
|---|------------------------------------|--------|
| 0 | /implement EFP-1423 (invoked)      | DONE   |
| 1 | jira-agent                         | DONE   |
| ... |
|12 | task-history finalized             | DONE (ai-brain/task-history/EFP-1423.md) |
```

### Good (HALT at completeness)
```
| # | Phase                              | Status |
|---|------------------------------------|--------|
| 0 | /implement EFP-1423 (invoked)      | DONE   |
| 1 | jira-agent                         | DONE   |
| 2 | ticket-completeness-agent          | HALTED |
| 3 | router-agent                       | N/A    |
| ... |
|12 | task-history finalized             | DONE (ai-brain/task-history/EFP-1423.md, phase=halted) |

## Halt reason
ticket-completeness-agent: missing AC + ticket unassigned. See "What you need to do" above.
```

### Bad
```
✅ Done! Pipeline complete.
Files: Column.tsx, ...
```
(no checklist; impossible to tell which phases ran or were skipped)

